  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together fish sauce, lime juice, grated ginger, sesame oil, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the cooked rice noodles to the bowl and toss to combine.",
    "In a separate bowl, mix together diced melons and shredded wood-fired-baked chicken.",
    "Add the melon and chicken mixture to the bowl with the noodles and toss to combine.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a baking dish and bake for 15 minutes.",
    "Remove the dish from the oven and garnish with chopped cilantro.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy.",
    "Let it cool completely before refrigerating or freezing for meal prep."
